From: Namecoin Integration <namecoin-integration@example.com>
Date: 2026-04-16
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] netwerk: Add network.namecoin.* preferences

Registers the about:config preferences used by nsNamecoinResolver:
  - network.namecoin.enabled                (boolean, default false)
  - network.namecoin.electrumx_servers      (string, default ws://electrumx.testls.space:50003)
  - network.namecoin.cache_ttl_seconds      (uint32, default 3600)
  - network.namecoin.require_tls            (boolean, default true)
  - network.namecoin.max_alias_hops         (uint32, default 5)
  - network.namecoin.connection_timeout_ms  (uint32, default 10000)
  - network.namecoin.query_multiple_servers (boolean, default true)

All prefs are off/disabled by default. The resolver is only active when
network.namecoin.enabled is set to true via about:config.

Phase 2 will add settings UI; for Phase 1 these are about:config only.

Bug: <to be filed on bugzilla.mozilla.org>
Reviewed-by: <pending>

---
 modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml | 60 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 60 insertions(+)

diff --git a/modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml b/modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml
index 00000001..00000002 100644
--- a/modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml
+++ b/modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.yaml
@@ -8500,6 +8500,66 @@
   value: true
   mirror: always
 
+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
+# network.namecoin.* — Namecoin (.bit) decentralized domain resolution
+#
+# Allows Firefox to resolve .bit domains via the Namecoin blockchain using
+# the ElectrumX JSON-RPC-over-WebSocket protocol. Disabled by default.
+#
+# Phase 1: DNS resolution only (A/AAAA records).
+# Phase 2 will add DANE-TLSA certificate validation.
+#
+# See: nsNamecoinResolver.{h,cpp} in netwerk/dns/
+# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
+
+- name: network.namecoin.enabled
+  type: bool
+  value: false
+  mirror: always
+  doc: >
+    Enable Namecoin (.bit) decentralized domain resolution via ElectrumX.
+    When true, .bit hostnames are resolved against the Namecoin blockchain
+    instead of system DNS. Disabled by default.
+
+- name: network.namecoin.electrumx_servers
+  type: DataMutexString
+  value: "ws://electrumx.testls.space:50003"
+  mirror: never
+  doc: >
+    Comma-separated list of ElectrumX server URLs (ws:// or wss://) for
+    Namecoin name resolution. Multiple servers provide redundancy and
+    cross-validation. Users should add their own trusted server.
+
+- name: network.namecoin.cache_ttl_seconds
+  type: uint32_t
+  value: 3600
+  mirror: always
+  doc: >
+    Cache TTL for resolved Namecoin names (seconds). Actual TTL may be
+    lower based on how many blocks remain before name expiry.
+
+- name: network.namecoin.require_tls
+  type: bool
+  value: true
+  mirror: always
+  doc: >
+    When true, refuse to load .bit pages over plain HTTP if TLSA records
+    exist in the name value. Only relevant after Phase 2 (TLS integration).
+
+- name: network.namecoin.max_alias_hops
+  type: uint32_t
+  value: 5
+  mirror: always
+  doc: >
+    Maximum number of alias chain hops to follow when a Namecoin name has
+    an "alias" field pointing to another .bit domain.
+
+- name: network.namecoin.connection_timeout_ms
+  type: uint32_t
+  value: 10000
+  mirror: always
+  doc: >
+    Timeout (milliseconds) for ElectrumX WebSocket connections.
+
+- name: network.namecoin.query_multiple_servers
+  type: bool
+  value: true
+  mirror: always
+  doc: >
+    When true, query multiple ElectrumX servers and cross-validate results
+    for increased security against malicious servers.
+
 # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
